{
  "text": "One interesting residue that is not visible in Fig. 12 , as it is hidden between chains A and C, is the homolog of E538 (Q421 in ASIC1). In ASIC1 structure, this Gln421 appears to be involved in intersubunit interactions with Asp79 of chain C [CITATION_1] . Mutation of E538 affected both cell surface delivery and self-inhibition (Figs. 6 and 9). Thus this result indicates that both cell surface delivery and self-inhibition are strongly dependent on subunit-subunit interactions.",
